# PHASE 5.11 — GLOBAL RULES ENFORCEMENT (Permanent Behavioral Patch)
# Effective Date: 2026-02-27
# Classification: NON-NEGOTIABLE — Violation = Architectural Failure
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# RULE 100: THE BFF PROXY PATTERN IS ABSOLUTE
#
# NEVER hardcode localhost, 127.0.0.1, or any absolute URL in client-side
# Next.js code (any file under src/app/ or src/components/ that runs in
# the browser). ALL API calls from the frontend MUST use relative paths
# (e.g., /api/payments, NOT http://localhost:8100/api/payments).
#
# When creating a NEW backend API endpoint that the frontend will consume:
#   1. Create the FastAPI route in fortress-guest-platform/backend/api/
#   2. Create a BFF proxy route at src/app/api/<domain>/[...path]/route.ts
#   3. Add the path prefix to the BFF_PREFIXES array in src/lib/api.ts
#   4. Verify the BFF proxy returns the correct HTTP status via curl on
#      port 3001 (NOT port 8100) before declaring the work complete
#
# If any of these four steps is skipped, the feature is NOT done.
# The browser NEVER talks to port 8100 directly. Period.

# RULE 101: ZERO-CRASH REACT STRICTNESS
#
# Every React component that accesses API data MUST be crash-proof:
#   - ALWAYS use optional chaining: data?.items?.length (never data.items.length)
#   - ALWAYS use nullish coalescing: data?.count ?? 0 (never assume values exist)
#   - ALWAYS add early returns: if (!data || !Array.isArray(data)) return null;
#   - ALWAYS guard .map(), .filter(), .reduce() calls with an Array.isArray() check
#     or optional chaining before invoking them
#   - ALWAYS wrap child components that receive API-sourced props in conditional
#     renders: {data.services && <ServicesGrid services={data.services} />}
#
# A white-screen crash from "Cannot read properties of undefined" is a
# P0 incident. The component must degrade gracefully, never explode.

# RULE 102: VERIFY BEFORE DEPLOYING — THE COMPLETE CIRCUIT
#
# Writing backend code is NOT the finish line. The complete circuit is:
#   1. Backend endpoint written and registered in main.py
#   2. BFF proxy route created in src/app/api/
#   3. BFF prefix registered in src/lib/api.ts
#   4. Frontend page/component created
#   5. curl verification on port 3001 confirms non-404 status codes
#   6. If Next.js is running in production mode (next start), rebuild
#      with next build and restart — source edits do NOT take effect
#      without a rebuild
#
# Do NOT tell the user "it should work now" until steps 1-6 are verified.
# Do NOT declare a feature complete with only the backend written.

# RULE 104: NEVER OVERWRITE WITHOUT READING
#
# Before writing, editing, or overwriting ANY existing file, you MUST
# read the current contents of that file first using the Read tool.
# This is NON-NEGOTIABLE. Blind writes cause regressions:
#   - Navigation links disappear
#   - Existing features are silently deleted
#   - Working code is replaced with partial rewrites
#
# The sequence is always: READ → understand → EDIT (surgical StrReplace).
# Prefer StrReplace over Write for existing files. Write is only for NEW files.
# If you use the Write tool on an existing file, you MUST have read it in
# the same conversation turn and you MUST preserve all existing content
# that is not explicitly being changed.
#
# Violating this rule is a P0 regression incident.

# RULE 103: NEVER BYPASS COMPILED STATE
#
# When modifying Python backend files in fortress-guest-platform/backend/:
#   1. Run: find backend -type d -name "__pycache__" -exec rm -rf {} +
#   2. Run: find backend -name "*.pyc" -delete
#   3. Kill the running process: fuser -k -9 8100/tcp
#   4. Wait 3 seconds for connections to drain
#   5. Restart: nohup python3 -m uvicorn backend.main:app --host 0.0.0.0
#      --port 8100 --log-level info > /tmp/fgp_restart.log 2>&1 &
#   6. Wait for startup, then verify: curl -s http://localhost:8100/health
#
# Stale .pyc files cause phantom bugs where new code appears to not work.
# ALWAYS purge bytecode cache before restarting after Python source changes.
#
# When modifying Next.js frontend files and the server runs in production
# mode (next start, not next dev):
#   1. Verify protected file exists: ls src/app/(dashboard)/page.tsx
#   2. Run: npx next build
#   3. Kill old server: fuser -k 3001/tcp
#   4. Restart: nohup npx next start -p 3001 > /tmp/nextjs_restart.log 2>&1 &
#   5. Verify: curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" http://localhost:3001
